This paper is about salient object detection using neural networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves edge preservation and multi-scale contextual analysis, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of RGB-D data, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a novel neural network architecture, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
